<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-05-19T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-05-19T11:00:00-05:00" n="225" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1426: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-05-19T11:00:00-05:00">May
                                        19, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 4:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>53. Reference the Legation’s despatch No. 741, May 6,<note n="30" xml:id="d225fn30">Not printed.</note> the Venezuelan member,
                                after consultation with his Government, approves sending Ocheltree
                                to Tegucigalpa on a technical errand for the Mediation Commission to
                                familiarize Honduran Government officials with geographic studies
                                now in the hands of the Permanent Secretariat at <pb facs="0171" n="163" xml:id="pg_163"/> San José. President of the Commission
                                has been informed through Ocheltree.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>